===Etymology===
* Found in the works of the 1100s CE [[Apabhramsha]] writer Vibudh Shridhar.
* Possibly derived from the Sanskrit words ''Hari'' (the Hindu god Vishnu) and ''ayana'' ("home"), meaning "the Abode of God".

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/hʌɹɪˈjɑːnə/|/hɑːɹɪˈjɑːnə/|lang=en}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
[[Image:Haryana in India (disputed hatched).svg|thumb|]]

# State in northern [[India]] which has [[union territory]] [[Chandigarh]] as its capital; [[Faridabad]] is its biggest city.

